    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "so you're basically saying a consensus exists and the \"protection\" side is just outdated or wrong. if the vast majority of economists and studies say they're bad, then isn't it more accurate to say that tariffs are just a failing policy rather than a \"complex challenge\"? isn't calling it a debate just being overly cautious when the evidence is so one-sided?",
